 way to bring the book's lessons to life. Uniquely, this book ties together the latest research on financing women-owned businesses and its implications for actual or potential entrepreneurs. Drawing on the Kauffman Firm Survey, a longitudinal survey of over 4,000 new firms, the authors are able to provide particularly useful conclusions, making this a must read for the thousands of women who are starting or may start businesses in the next few years. Click here to view the book trailer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aBusinesswomen -- United States. 0aBusinesswomenzUnited States. 0aWomen-owned business enterprises -- United States -- Finance. 0aWomen-owned business enterpriseszUnited StatesxFinance. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Finance / General.2bisacsh1 aRobb, Alicia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478167140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804781671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804781671/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles